   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pain relief for 500 hospice patients in Hungary</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project serves improving the quality of life of 500 terminally ill children and adults, who are cared for by the professionals of Hungarian Hospice Foundation per year. In order to save the cancer patients&apos; human dignity pain and other symptoms must be effectively controlled until the very end. We prefer caring for the patients in their own homes, especially in the case of pediatric patients. Our inpatient unit in Budapest is also available when hospitalization is needed.</narrative>
  </description>
